We’re back! @_astridedwards_ and I are returning for season 2 of Anonymous Was a Woman, the best book talk going around - courtesy of @futurewomen and @mccabehelen. Today we’re talking solitude, the quiet benefits of being alone, and the books which celebrate exactly that. We kick off season two with a discussion of our podcast namesake A Room of One’s Own by Virginia Woolf and then later this week we speak to Miles Franklin 2020 Award winner @tara_june_winch , from lockdown in France. Settle in for a bumper season of the podcast, which is available now on Apple iTunes! (Link to the newest episode is in my bio).

node.text: I’ve been missing going to shows so much lately. I miss seeing the bands I love & hanging out with my friends at some of my favorite venues. Unfortunately due to COVID-19 a lot of my favorite local venues are in jeopardy of closing their doors permanently. So I was taking a bath tonight, as I do, & I thought that I wanted to do something to help. It may not be much, but thinking about making this design I created into a sticker to sell. Proceeds will go towards all local venues that are having a hard time. Some of these places are like a 2nd home to me & I consider some of the people I’ve met family. ? #atlantamusicscene #atlanta #music #fortheatlantamusicscene #atlantamusic #design #illustration #artist #atlantaartist #secondhome #quarantine #quarantinethings #rad #life

node.text:
Happy Madras day ?!
I know, there are so many other things to celebrate about today. Maybe, you aren't having the best year till now but doesn't mean we should not celebrate the city which holds the people and so many cultures together. Madras (not chennai okay?) is not just a place or city. It is an emotion, I know it's a cliched say but If you felt what I just said then I guess you know what I mean ??. I always had this idea, when school gets over, while others were planning to go on vacation to hill stations and foreign cities, I wanted to go on a long drive just around Madras. See the beauty it holds like no other city. Which unfortunately I couldn't as expected but I did that's when I decided I have to make a post just for this city which has taught me so much.
I tried my best to put in all the things that I loved and I noticed if I missed anything please comment that down. If you loved this doodle please give it a heart  and share it with others & celebrate Madras with me ?.
.
.

INSULTÓ, AGREDIÓ Y FUE DETENIDA:

El hecho ocurrió en la Estación Monte Grande de la Linea Roca.

Todo sucedió a raíz de la verificación de los permisos de circulación que estaban realizando efectivos de la Policía Federal.

Al momento de la verificación, llegó una mujer que según informaron, no poseía el permiso de circulación. Ante esta situación, los efectivos le negaron el ingreso, por lo qué la mujer comenzó a alterarse.

Tras insultar a los efectivos, se retiró, pero minutos después regresó y comenzó a filmar e insultar a un efectivo. Segundos después, filma a la oficial que le decía a su compañero, "dejala","dejala" y le pega con la mano al celular de la agente que estaba registrado el hecho.

Después de los insultos y agresión, los efectivos procedieron a la detención

"Ayúdenme, me quiero levantar, para loco, nadie está haciendo nada, llámale a mi mamá", decía la mujer ya aprehendida.

***Warning I’m in progress***
This is hard for me to post because I hate that I let myself get this unhealthy! I lost who I was and what I enjoyed doing. This isn’t about body shaming because I’m beautiful no matter what. I want to be someone’s motivation to get up for yourself and do something to better your health. I started during this pandemic and have no plans to stop. I have a long way to go but I wanted to share my progress. I did this on my own even when others tried to stop me and discourage me. I had my bad days and good days but I kept pushing. If you have anything negative to say keep it to yourself & look inside yourself on why you feel the need to bring others down. *Life Update: It's been a while?*

I've been back home for a solid 5 months now & if this year so far has taught me anything, it's not to take anything for granted.

This time's been so productive and calming for me lately since I took a small break from social media. I'm really enjoying the slower change of pace in my life for now.

So my plans have obviously changed (temporarily) but the end goals are the same with school & badminton. This was a blessing in disguise but I had to get creative during this time. I got to rest mentally, spend more time with family & study more?

I hope everyone's well & making the most of the current situation.

Hi...i've been through your page.. it is really amazing. Do check mine??

A newly organized space that still looks good makes me happy!

Today Clara and I made some space for her school stuff in my office bookcase. To say it was torturous is an understatement. Not my favorite activity to do with a five year old but I want her to keep her excitement about school.

We have all her books accessible and hid the pencils, markers and pens in those boxes so Rose will be less likely to find them and get into anything she shouldn’t. It was a good activity for Clara to arrange what’s in the boxes the way she wants and I don’t have to look at it.

I realize it won’t stay this way but I can also clean it when I sit at my desk and can’t focus. ? #enneagram1 problems I’m work through. I would say I’ve made a lot of progress in this area since having kids.

I’ll be sharing all the spaces I’m organizing and purging in stories for the next week so make sure you follow along. Join in and tag me if you want too!

I feel like this is round two or three or purging since coronavirus, anyone else in the same boat?

? ????? ???? ??? ???? ??? ????? ???, ?? ????? ???? ??? ???? ??? ????? ????... ??
.
.
.
. 
.
Sí, hay días donde no soy el rebelde que entra a lugares prohibidos y gira por los aires... Aunque la verdad lo sigo siendo, sólo que disfrazado, ese disfraz de esta sociedad cuadrada, peinado y con camisa. // Desde que tengo memoria siempre he sido un 'outcast', siempre formando parte de la minoría y usualmente siendo el raro del grupo. Hay días en los que me gustaría volver y decirle a aquel chico de 14 años lleno de miedos que ser diferente sería lo mejor y más auténtico de sí, y lo mucho que eso le ayudaría a no formar parte de esa escala de grises a la que la mayoría quiere pertenecer. Muchos se olvidan de quiénes son, de sus sueños, de sus ideas, y mucho tiempo me criticaron (y a la fecha) por salir de Medicina, cuando realmente eso era lo que me hundía y me hizo sentir triste durante mucho tiempo. Eran pocas las personas en esa carrera que me ayudaron a sobrevivir a eso y, son personas a quienes no puedo dejar de agradecer por sacarle colores y vida a algo que me consumía y nadie más veía. En fin, si llegas a este punto del texto, no complazcas a nadie, nunca vamos a tener contento a este mundo. Y si te dicen que pareces un niño pequeño entonces actúa como uno, sueña, ríete de todo a tu alrededor, llena de colores las paredes y lanza la televisión por la ventana. F*ck this square world. 
.
.
.
.

A thought about covid 19: ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
it doesn’t seem real until it affects someone you know and love PERSONALLY. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
i think this can be said about a lot of people and is a major reason why parties and gatherings are still happening despite the need to social distance. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
some people may not be wearing masks because they feel it’s their right. or they may keep gathering because they’re bored in quarantine. i get it. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
but then they find out their mom, or their dad, or their sibling, got covid so now they wear masks. now they take the precautions that they should’ve been taking the entire time. but the exposure has already been done.⁣⁣
⁣⁣
it also hit me yesterday when i found out that a close family friend was intubated and sedated in our icu due to covid. it broke my heart. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
it hits home. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
don’t you think it would be a shame to keep losing the people we love because we’re not taking this pandemic seriously?
.
